From the model results we see that the the parameter for TAX and INDUS are not significantly different from zero at 5% significance level. (because the confidence interval for its coefficient includes zero and the p-value is very high than the significance level of 0.05)

Parameter for all the remaining features, on the other hand, are significantly different from zero. (because the corresponding confidence interval includes zero and the p-value is almost zero.(lower than 0.05 significane level)

Hence we can conclude that the increase/decrease in TAX can't play a significant role in the Median Value of owner occupied houses so we can remove Feature TAX from the features

also higher/lower in INDUS can't play a significant role in the Median Value of owner occupied houses so we can remove Feature INDUS from the features

Let's now test our inference and drop the TAX variable and use all the other Variables as Features of the data to predict the Median Value of the owner-occupied house[MV]

Interpreting Coefficient of the Predictors:

1) With the Increase of Crime rate by 1% we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes reduced by 131.3 USD

2) With the Increase of Nitric Oxide Concentration percentage by 1% we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes reduced by 1761 USD

3) With the Increase of Number of rooms by [lets say 1 room] we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes increases by 6640 USD

4) With the Increase of AGE by 1 year we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes reduced by 0593 USD

5) With the Increase of Weighted Distance to five boston employment centers by 1KM we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes reduced by 1263 USD

6) With the Increase of Peoples teacher ratio by 1% we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes reduced by 0985 USD

7) With the Increase of proportion of Blacks by 1% we expect the Median value of owner occupied homes reduced by 10.5 USD

Variance Inflation Factor¶

In [422]:
def vif_summary(input_data, dependent_col):
    x_vars = input_data.drop([dependent_col],axis=1)
    xvar_names=x_vars.columns
    for i in range(0,xvar_names.shape[0]):
        y=x_vars[xvar_names[i]]
        x=x_vars[xvar_names.drop(xvar_names[i])]
        rsquare=sm.OLS(y,x).fit().rsquared
        vif=round(1/(1-rsquare),2)
        print(xvar_names[i],"VIF=",vif)

def vif_summary(input_data, dependent_col):
    x_vars = input_data.drop([dependent_col],axis=1)
    xvar_names=x_vars.columns
    for i in range(0,xvar_names.shape[0]):
        y=x_vars[xvar_names[i]]
        x=x_vars[xvar_names.drop(xvar_names[i])]
        rsquare=sm.OLS(y,x).fit().rsquared
        vif=round(1/(1-rsquare),2)
        print(xvar_names[i],"VIF=",vif)
